Soft boiled eggs, for example, simply need to be brought to boiling point from cold water, removed from the heat and then left to sit for 4-5 minutes depending on their size. Small new potatoes only need to be boiled for five minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and leave them to sit for 15 minutes. Similarly, carrots and other vegetables can be removed from the heat as soon as the water reaches boiling point.
